      "id": "intro-0",
      "sectionId": "intro",
      "title": "Intro",
      "body": "This is a quick reference cheat sheet to getting started with linux bash shell scripting."
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-1",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "hello.sh",
      "body": "%60%60%60bash%0A%23!%2Fbin%2Fbash%0A%0AVAR%3D%22world%22%0Aecho%20%22Hello%20%24VAR!%22%20%23%20%3D%3E%20Hello%20world!%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AExecute%20the%20script%0A%0A%60%60%60shell%20script%0A%24%20bash%20hello.sh%0A%0A%60%60%60%0A%0A%23%23%23%20Variables%0A%0A%60%60%60bash%0ANAME%3D%22John%22%0A%0Aecho%20%24%7BNAME%7D%20%20%20%20%23%20%3D%3E%20John%20(Variables)%0Aecho%20%24NAME%20%20%20%20%20%20%23%20%3D%3E%20John%20(Variables)%0Aecho%20%22%24NAME%22%20%20%20%20%23%20%3D%3E%20John%20(Variables)%0Aecho%20'%24NAME'%20%20%20%20%23%20%3D%3E%20%24NAME%20(Exact%20string)%0Aecho%20%22%24%7BNAME%7D!%22%20%23%20%3D%3E%20John!%20(Variables)%0A%0ANAME%20%3D%20%22John%22%20%20%20%23%20%3D%3E%20Error%20(about%20space)%0A%60%60%60",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-5",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Comments",
      "body": "%60%60%60bash%0A%23%20This%20is%20an%20inline%20Bash%20comment.%0A%60%60%60%0A%0A%60%60%60bash%0A%3A%20'%0AThis%20is%20a%0Avery%20neat%20comment%0Ain%20bash%0A'%0A%60%60%60%0A%0AMulti-line%20comments%20use%20%60%3A'%60%20to%20open%20and%20%60'%60%20to%20close",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-7",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Arguments",
      "body": "| Expression  | Description                           |\n| ----------- | ------------------------------------- |\n| `$1` … `$9` | Parameter 1 ... 9                     |\n| `$0`        | Name of the script itself             |\n| `$1`        | First argument                        |\n| `${10}`     | Positional parameter 10               |\n| `$#`        | Number of arguments                   |\n| `$$`        | Process id of the shell               |\n| `$*`        | All arguments                         |\n| `$@`        | All arguments, starting from first    |\n| `$-`        | Current options                       |\n| `$_`        | Last argument of the previous command |\n\nSee: [Special parameters](http://wiki.bash-hackers.org/syntax/shellvars#special_parameters_and_shell_variables)"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-9",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Functions",
      "body": "%60%60%60bash%0Aget_name()%20%7B%0A%20%20%20%20echo%20%22John%22%0A%7D%0A%0Aecho%20%22You%20are%20%24(get_name)%22%0A%60%60%60%0A%0ASee%3A%20%5BFunctions%5D(%23bash-functions)",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-11",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Conditionals",
      "body": "%60%60%60bash%0Aif%20%5B%5B%20-z%20%22%24string%22%20%5D%5D%3B%20then%0A%20%20%20%20echo%20%22String%20is%20empty%22%0Aelif%20%5B%5B%20-n%20%22%24string%22%20%5D%5D%3B%20then%0A%20%20%20%20echo%20%22String%20is%20not%20empty%22%0Afi%0A%60%60%60%0A%0ASee%3A%20%5BConditionals%5D(%23bash-conditionals)",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-13",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Brace expansion",
      "body": "```bash\necho {A,B}.js\n```\n\n| Expression | Description         |\n| ---------- | ------------------- |\n| `{A,B}`    | Same as `A B`       |\n| `{A,B}.js` | Same as `A.js B.js` |\n| `{1..5}`   | Same as `1 2 3 4 5` |\n\nSee: [Brace expansion](http://wiki.bash-hackers.org/syntax/expansion/brace)"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-16",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Shell%20execution",
      "body": "%60%60%60bash%0A%23%20%3D%3E%20I'm%20in%20%2Fpath%2Fof%2Fcurrent%0Aecho%20%22I'm%20in%20%24(PWD)%22%0A%0A%23%20Same%20as%3A%0Aecho%20%22I'm%20in%20%60pwd%60%22%0A%60%60%60%0A%0ASee%3A%20%5BCommand%20substitution%5D(http%3A%2F%2Fwiki.bash-hackers.org%2Fsyntax%2Fexpansion%2Fcmdsubst)",
      "encoded": true
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-18",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Syntax",
      "body": "| Code              | Description         |\n| ----------------- | ------------------- |\n| `${FOO%suffix}`   | Remove suffix       |\n| `${FOO#prefix}`   | Remove prefix       |\n| `${FOO%%suffix}`  | Remove long suffix  |\n| `${FOO##prefix}`  | Remove long prefix  |\n| `${FOO/from/to}`  | Replace first match |\n| `${FOO//from/to}` | Replace all         |\n| `${FOO/%from/to}` | Replace suffix      |\n| `${FOO/#from/to}` | Replace prefix      |"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-19",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Substrings",
      "body": "| Expression      | Description                    |\n| --------------- | ------------------------------ |\n| `${FOO:0:3}`    | Substring _(position, length)_ |\n| `${FOO:(-3):3}` | Substring from the right       |"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-20",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Length",
      "body": "| Expression | Description      |\n| ---------- | ---------------- |\n| `${#FOO}`  | Length of `$FOO` |"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-21",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Default values",
      "body": "| Expression        | Description                              |\n| ----------------- | ---------------------------------------- |\n| `${FOO:-val}`     | `$FOO`, or `val` if unset                |\n| `${FOO:=val}`     | Set `$FOO` to `val` if unset             |\n| `${FOO:+val}`     | `val` if `$FOO` is set                   |\n| `${FOO:?message}` | Show message and exit if `$FOO` is unset |"
    },
